  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminalization of money laundering activities\n- Mandatory reporting of large cash transactions\n- Enhanced due diligence for high-risk customers\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Regulatory oversight by central banks\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Civil and criminal penalties\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Financial institutions must implement AML programs\n- Customer identification procedures\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Regular risk assessments\n\n6. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Extradition agreements\n- Joint investigative efforts\n\n7. Specific Areas of Focus\n- Cryptocurrency transactions\n- Cross-border financial transfers\n- Real estate transactions\n- High-value asset exchanges\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities.",
